    "body": "# Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist\n\n- [x] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [x] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [x] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n\nThis PR fixes two issues when running the ModelOpt Gemma3 NVFP4/FP8 model:\n\n- KV cache scale naming mismatch.\n- Incorrect vision model quantization assumption: The current vLLM workflow assumes that Gemma3’s vision model weights are quantized to NVFP4 or FP8. For NVFP4 it halves the last dimension of the weight tensor. In reality, ModelOpt does not quantize these weights in the checkpoint, leading to a tensor shape mismatch.\n\nThis PR also fixes a few environment issues (mxfp4 and torch._inductor related) and make the workflow more robust. \n\n## Purpose\n\n## Test Plan\n```\nfrom vllm import LLM, SamplingParams\nimport os\nos.environ['VLLM_ATTENTION_BACKEND'] = \"FLASH_ATTN\"\nos.environ['VLLM_USE_STANDALONE_COMPILE'] = \"0\"\ndef main():\n\n    model_id = \"Gemma-3-12b-it_nvfp4\"\n    sampling_params = SamplingParams(temperature=0.8, top_p=0.9)\n\n    prompts = [\n        \"Hello, my name is\",\n        \"The president of the United States is\",\n        \"The capital of France is\",\n        \"The future of AI is\",\n    ]\n\n    llm = LLM(model=model_id, quantization=\"modelopt_fp4\", tensor_parallel_size=4, trust_remote_code=True, max_model_len=1024)\n    outputs = llm.generate(prompts, sampling_params)\n\n    for output in outputs:\n        prompt = output.prompt\n        generated_text = output.outputs[0].text\n        print(f\"Prompt: {prompt!r}, Generated text: {generated_text!r}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n\"Gemma-3-12b-it_nvfp4\" is a NVFP4 checkpoint quantized with [ModelOpt](https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-Model-Optimizer/tree/main/examples/llm_ptq).\n\n## Test Result\n```\nPrompt: 'Hello, my name is', Generated text: \" Michael and I'm a professional voice actor. I'm here to provide\"\nPrompt: 'The president of the United States is', Generated text: ' facing an unprecedented level of scrutiny and criticism for his handling of the COVID-1'\nPrompt: 'The capital of France is', Generated text: ' Paris.\\nParis is the capital of France.\\nThe capital of France is'\nPrompt: 'The future of AI is', Generated text: \" looking bright, but also complex. We're seeing rapid advancements, and it\"\n```\n## (Optional) Documentation Update\n\n",
